abstract: Many questions remain about a potential Senate trial. Also, we preview Thursday’s Democratic debate.

headline_main: Here’s What We’re Watching After Impeachment

abstract: The congresswoman, a Hawaii Democrat, called impeachment “a partisan process, fueled by tribal animosities” and said she favored censure instead.
snippet: The congresswoman, a Hawaii Democrat, called impeachment “a partisan process, fueled by tribal animosities” and said she favored censure instead.
lead_paragraph: Representative Tulsi Gabbard, a Hawaii Democrat and 2020 presidential candidate, broke with most members of her party on Wednesday and voted “present” on the two articles of impeachment charging President Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
lead_paragraph: CLINTON, Iowa — Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
headline_main: Seeking Fresh Momentum, Democrat Warren Recalibrates 'Medicare for All' Rhetoric
headline_print_headline: Seeking Fresh Momentum, Democrat Warren Recalibrates 'Medicare for All' Rhetoric

abstract: On a day when the U.S. House of Representatives debated whether President Donald Trump should be removed from office, members of his administration fanned out across the country to make the case that the president is steadily getting the job done.
snippet: On a day when the U.S. House of Representatives debated whether President Donald Trump should be removed from office, members of his administration fanned out across the country to make the case that the president is steadily getting the job done....
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On a day when the U.S. House of Representatives debated whether President Donald Trump should be removed from office, members of his administration fanned out across the country to make the case that the president is steadily getting the job done.
headline_main: As Impeachment Looms, Trump Officials Look to Change the Subject
headline_print_headline: As Impeachment Looms, Trump Officials Look to Change the Subject

abstract: From Boston to Albuquerque to Atlanta, Americans mostly averted their gaze as impeachment proceedings shook Washington.
snippet: From Boston to Albuquerque to Atlanta, Americans mostly averted their gaze as impeachment proceedings shook Washington.
lead_paragraph: It was a momentous day in American history. But, by all indications, it was not a momentous day in the lives of most Americans.

abstract: A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second term.
snippet: A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second te...
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second term.

abstract: President Donald Trump’s expansion of a program aimed at steering more veterans to private health care is getting an $8.9 billion boost as part of the massive government spending bill approved by the House, setting up a potential battle over the direction of the Veterans Affairs Department.
snippet: President Donald Trump’s expansion of a program aimed at steering more veterans to private health care is getting an $8.9 billion boost as part of the massive government spending bill approved by the House, setting up a potential battle over the d...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump’s expansion of a program aimed at steering more veterans to private health care is getting an $8.9 billion boost as part of the massive government spending bill approved by the House, setting up a potential battle over the direction of the Veterans Affairs Department.
headline_main: Budget Deal Advances VA Private Care Program Backed by Trump
headline_print_headline: Budget Deal Advances VA Private Care Program Backed by Trump

abstract: As he campaigns, Mr. Biden offers free-flowing analysis about the race he’s running in. Among his takes: He should be described as the front-runner, and he’s best positioned to beat President Trump.
snippet: As he campaigns, Mr. Biden offers free-flowing analysis about the race he’s running in. Among his takes: He should be described as the front-runner, and he’s best positioned to beat President Trump.
lead_paragraph: DECORAH, Iowa — Joseph R. Biden Jr. insists he is the front-runner in the Democratic primary race. He cites polling in battleground states. He suggests that his coattails would help down-ballot candidates win around the country. And he worries aloud about how his answer to a given question might play in the news media (“No matter how I answer that, I’m going to get clobbered,” he observed recently aboard his campaign bus).
